The Shibboleth Service Provider SSO-enables and Federation-enables web
applications written with any programming language or framework. It
integrates natively with popular web servers like Apache and IIS.

A loosely coupled integration strategy allows you to support SAML,
rich attribute-exchange, and many value-added features, often without
significantly changing your application code or using proprietary
interfaces.

This requires xerces-c, log4shib, xml-security-c, xmltooling, opensaml.

You will need to add the following line to /etc/httpd/httpd.conf:
  Include /etc/httpd/extra/mod_shib.conf
